Unveil {3}
When The Ætherist is unveiled, counter target spell. At the beginning of target player's next main phase, they gain life and add an amount of {C} equal to that spell's mana value.

Undercover
Unveil {X}
When The Augur is unveiled, target player shuffles, scries X, then exiles the top card of their library. They gain life equal to twice that card's mana value, then they may cast it without paying its mana cost.

Undercover
Unveil {X}
When The Cryomancer is unveiled, tap X target permanents and remove them from combat. If it's your turn, distribute X stun counters among any number of those permanents. (If a permanent with a stun counter would become untapped, remove one from it instead.)

Undercover
Unveil {2}
When The Great Martyr is unveiled, until end of turn, if a source an opponent controls would deal damage to a Leader player, that damage is dealt to you instead. The same is true for losing life, discarding cards and sacrificing permanents. Whenever you are dealt damage or lose life this way, draw half that many cards, rounded up. Whenever you discard a card or sacrifice a permanent this way, you gain 2 life.

